<i>When I say I don't remember that day,
I'm not lying.</i>

01:05.536 --> 01:07.924
<i>I wish I did,
but I just don't.</i>

01:08.683 --> 01:10.915
<i>Sometimes the most
important stuff goes away.</i>

01:12.429 --> 01:15.939
<i>It goes away so bad,
it's like it was never there to begin with.</i>

01:18.573 --> 01:21.188
<i>It's funny,
the stuff that sticks in your head.</i>

01:21.649 --> 01:24.700
<i>I could tell you forward and backward
about some day when I was five,</i>

01:25.127 --> 01:27.447
<i>and my dad bought me
a stupid ice-cream cone.</i>

01:27.930 --> 01:30.155
<i>I could tell you the
flavour of the ice cream...</i>

01:30.528 --> 01:33.230
<i>Was... pink bubble gum.</i>

01:33.673 --> 01:36.359
<i>...and even stuff about
the girl who scooped it out.</i>

01:36.689 --> 01:38.771
<i>Her hair was fire red.</i>

01:40.269 --> 01:43.707
<i>All that stuff is there like
it was happening right now, but...</i>

01:44.100 --> 01:46.106
<i>I don't remember that day.</i>

01:46.489 --> 01:48.902
<i>At least, not the stuff
that they want me to.</i>

01:51.378 --> 01:54.508
<i>I remember it was the
first really hot day of spring.</i>

01:55.518 --> 01:58.977
<i>I remember how the sun felt
on the back of my neck.</i>

02:00.098 --> 02:02.021
<i>That's about it.</i>

02:02.615 --> 02:05.098
<i>Here's another one
of those things that sticks.</i>

02:05.587 --> 02:08.461
<i>This one is something
a friend of mine said to me.</i>

02:08.952 --> 02:12.853
<i>"You have to believe that life is more
than the sum of its parts, kiddo. "</i>

02:13.302 --> 02:16.212
<i>I remember it right
down to that "kiddo" part.</i>

02:16.879 --> 02:21.059
<i>But when I think about what she said,
the same thing always comes into my head...</i>

02:23.534 --> 02:27.004
<i>What if you can't put the pieces
together in the first place?</i>

02:43.035 --> 02:46.608
# And this I know,
his teeth as white as snow

02:47.114 --> 02:50.545
